I doubt that Lien is &quot;out there&quot; laughing at us as I doubt that she even cares enough about this thread after she said her goodbyes. As you, flamingly, pointed out to her, she is twenty two and in college. I agree with the &quot;old farts&quot; part.<br><br>
Now, your last post is much more to my liking. Honest, direct and no bullshit, no games, no distractions. The only tactic that I, knowingly, employed, was being honest and direct and hanging on your ass like a bulldog. Granted, I went off the deep end (just a tad) when you hit me with your being Jewish, the timing was just right for that, but, I am sure, many think I had lost it months ago, so, what the fuck, over(Nam talk)! Oh, yeah, and I can clean up my language a bit, I admit.<br><br>
We are not going to get any closer on the issue of assimilation or anything else with the Vietnamese. You are the one with the anger, the hostility. You are the one who is bothered by that sign. You own all that shit. I am the one who doesn't feel this way, at least not about the Vietnamese, or any other racial group. Anger about other things, yes, enough to power a dynamo, but not about any racial group. If you want to hang onto it, be my guest. I had hoped you wouldn't want to, but, your choice.<br><br>
Saying that, doc, I will bite you in the ass (affectionately, of course) and I will point out the games that are played that I believe is racist in nature, intentionally or not, or is destructive. The fact that you don't see the hurts, bother me.<br><br>
As far as where I am coming from, Doc, I've been telling you all along. 1. I will stand up to racism, or to racist behavior. Many, not just myself, have been trying to point things out to you; you don't want to hear. 2.I want you to not feel those &quot;bad&quot; feelings that you had admitted to. But, you want to hang onto them. 3. To get you to see the hurt and pain that you inflict on others. Others have tried for you to see, but, again, closed eyes.<br><br>
That's it! That was my agenda in its entirety. Nothing more<br>
But, as the gallery has informed us, its time to move on.<br><br>
You have pointed out, and rightly so, that I lack humor. I believe that there is little humor in any pages on this site, its all too deadly serious. Saying that, I accept your trying to interject humor by calling me Mr. and thus, I chuckle. Chuckle, chuckle! <br><br>
But, it is apparent to everyone that I have not given my name to any on the site. The reasons are mine and mine alone, I need not justify these reasons to anyone. Everyone but you had respected that. And, because you do not see this, nor understand, is what frustrates and infuriates me.<br>
That you did not recognize how I valued my need to keep it to myself on site.  That you cannot see the need for others not to put their e-mail addresses on site. That you, at times, strike out and cause pain. That you, at times, displays racists attitudes.<br><br>
Look, doc, this is it for me. We have come full circle.  It truely is my desire that, one day, there will be someone that will be able to take a bit of your blinders off. It is apparent that this is not time for you. In all of this, Doc, I have never threatened with pulling away my friendship. I don't leave my friends in the bush. <br><br>
When I bite you in the ass, its very personal. You think I would bother with my enemies?<br><br>

